parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS control module can cause the loss of anti-lock braking functionality, leading to increased stopping distances and potential accidents.
symptoms: The ABS light and brake light on the dashboard may illuminate
accompanied by a beeping or buzzing sound. The ABS system may not engage when needed
and the brake pedal may feel soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent ABS failure can lead to unexpected loss of anti-lock braking functionality, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The ABS light and brake light on the dashboard may intermittently illuminate
accompanied by a beeping or buzzing sound. The ABS system may not engage when needed
and the brake pedal may feel soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: ABS failure in cold weather can increase the risk of accidents, especially in snowy or icy conditions.
symptoms: The ABS light and brake light on the dashboard may illuminate in cold weather
accompanied by a beeping or buzzing sound. The ABS system may not engage when needed
and the brake pedal may feel soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing belt can cause the engine to stall or seize, leading to loss of power and control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or dies
the timing belt breaks
the engine makes a loud noise
the vehicle loses power
the check engine light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the water pump can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, stalling, or seizing, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine overheats
the water pump leaks
the timing belt fails
the engine makes a loud noise
the vehicle loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch master cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cam seals can cause oil leaks, leading to engine damage, stalling, or seizing, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Oil leaks from the engine cam seals
the engine makes a loud noise
the vehicle loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause the airbags to deploy unexpectedly or not deploy at all in the event of a crash, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag system malfunctions
the airbags deploy unexpectedly
the airbags do not deploy in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle can cause loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
the accelerator pedal sticks
the vehicle is difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tie rod can cause loss of steering control, leading to accidents or difficulty maneuvering the vehicle.
symptoms: Squeaking or grinding noise when turning
clunking noise from the front wheel
vibration when driving
wandering or pulling to one side
difficulty steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering linkage can cause loss of steering control, leading to accidents or difficulty maneuvering the vehicle.
symptoms: Grinding noise when turning
vibration when driving
difficulty steering.
